Git is the industry-standard version control system for web developer
Use Git commands to help keep track of changes made to a project
* git init creates a new Git repository
* git status inspects the contents of the working directory and staging area
* git add: add files from the working area to staging area
* git diff: show the different between staging area and working area
* git commit: permanently store file changes from staging area in the resposity
* git log: show a list of all previous commits
